description: URL path to link to this future. Should not include the basePath.

description: Whether or not this link should be shown on the front page of Kibana.

description: An ordinal used to sort features relative to one another for display on the home page

interfaces.label: AppLinkData
description: This type is used by consumers to register a new app link for a sample dataset.

children.label: sampleObject
description: The sample object that is used for this app link's path; if the path does not use an object ID, set this to null.

children.label: getPath
description:
Function that returns the path for this app link. Note that the `objectId` can be different than the given `sampleObject.id`, depending
on how the sample data was installed. If the `sampleObject` is null, the `objectId` argument will be an empty string.

children.label: label
description: The label for this app link.

children.label: icon
description: The icon for this app link.

interfaces.label: SampleObject
description: This type is used to identify an object in a sample dataset.

children.label: type
description: The type of the sample object.

children.label: id
description: The ID of the sample object.
